ml.alternet.parser

Annotation Type Grammar.Skip


  • @Documented
 @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Target(value={FIELD,TYPE})
public static @interface Grammar.Skip
    Indicates the characters to skip (typically, some whitespaces) before and after parsing a token. When set on a grammar, the annotation is inherited on every field that is not a Grammar.Fragment and that doesn't override this annotation. Anonymous subrules or subrules from other grammars are not affected.
    Author:
    Philippe Poulard

    • Required Element Summary

      Required Elements 
      Modifier and Type Required Element and Description
      String token
      The name of the token field that define the characters to skip.

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      boolean after
      Skip the characters after the token.
      boolean before
      Skip the characters before the token.
      Class<? extends Grammar> grammar
      Indicates the grammar that host the char token.

    • Element Detail

      • token

        public abstract String token
        The name of the token field that define the characters to skip. May be $empty to override the grammar Skip annotation for disable skipping. The field that define the characters to skip is defined in the same grammar of the annotated field, except if the grammar attribute is set. If the annotation is set on a grammar and that the target token is in the same grammar, the token is not affected by the Skip annotation set on the grammar and must not have it on itself. The target token may be arbitrary complex as long as it is exposed as a token. None of the subrules can be annotated with Skip.
        Returns:
        The name of the token field in the grammar.
        See Also:
        Grammar.CharToken

      • grammar

        public abstract Class<? extends Grammar> grammar
        Indicates the grammar that host the char token. When missing, the default value Grammar.class means that the grammar is the same grammar of the annotated field.
        Returns:
        The grammar.
        Default:
        ml.alternet.parser.Grammar.class

      • before

        public abstract boolean before
        Skip the characters before the token.
        Returns:
        true by default.
        Default:
        true

      • after

        public abstract boolean after
        Skip the characters after the token.
        Returns:
        true by default.
        Default:
        true
